at the aesthetics and oeuvre of Juana Borrero y Pierra (1877–1896), one of the most important and yet little-known representatives of Cuban Modernismo. Her aesthetics of the wholeness of art and life unfolds in the artist’s poems, literary love letters, drawings, paintings, and literary prose, produced in the light of late Cuban modernism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBiographie. 4aBorrero, Juana. 4aKubanische Literatur. 4aModernismo. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh  aBorrero, Juana.  aCuban literature.  abiography.  amodernismo.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107485740 cprintz978311074835240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074849940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110748499423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110748499/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023